content: <?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>  <reference anchor='I-D.zuniga-mif-802-21-overview'> <front> <title>IEEE 802.21 Overview</title>  <author initials='J' surname='Z\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffdiga' fullname='Juan-Carlos Z\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd\ufffdiga'>     <organization /> </author>  <author initials='P' surname='Seite' fullname='Pierrick Seite'>     <organization /> </author>  <date month='February' day='14' year='2014' />  <abstract><t>Some of the messages defined by a potential MIF API may rely on functionalities provided by lower layers.  The IEEE 802.21 specification defines an abstraction of lower layer functions that can be useful for a MIF API.  This document provides an overview of the IEEE 802.21 specification and enumerates a subset of functions that can be used in the context of the MIF API to interact with lower layers.</t></abstract>  </front>  <seriesInfo name='Internet-Draft' value='draft-zuniga-mif-802-21-overview-02' /> <format type='TXT'         target='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-zuniga-mif-802-21-overview-02.txt' /> </reference>
